pr_review_comment_body:
I noticed that the python docs say

> To extend this to recognize other objects, subclass and implement a default() method with another method that returns a serializable object for o if possible, otherwise it should call the superclass implementation (to raise TypeError).

And their example of a custom `default()` looks like this:

```python
def default(self, o):
   try:
       iterable = iter(o)
   except TypeError:
       pass
   else:
       return list(iterable)
   # Let the base class default method raise the TypeError
   return JSONEncoder.default(self, o)
```

So, I think your custom encoder should change to:

```python
class FailProofJSONEncoder(json.JSONEncoder):
    def default(self, o):
        try:
            return repr(o)
        except Exception:
            return super(FailProofJSONEncoder, self).default(o)
```

In case the call to `repr()` fails.

great! Try to improve this method even more, see the following example code:

```python
errors = []
for field in ['certificate', 'private_key']:
    try:
        crypto.load_certificate(crypto.FILETYPE_PEM, getattr(self, field))
    except OpenSSL.crypto.Error as e:
        errors.append(ValidationError({
            field: _('OpenSSL error: {0}'.format(e.args[0]))}
        ))
if errors:
    raise ValidationError(errors)
```

See the [django docs about raising multiple errors](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.11/ref/forms/validation/#raising-multiple-errors) to understand what the proposed code does.
